gop-voters-lawsuit-disqualifying-trump-colorado-ballot-supreme-court-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERepublican%20voters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Colorado%20who%20argued%20Trump%20was%20ineligible%20to%20appear%20on%20the%20ballot%20because%20he%20engaged%20in%20insurrection%20by%20encouraging%20his%20supporters%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20to%20storm%20the%20Capitol%20during%20the%20congressional%20certification%20of%20President%20Joe%20Biden's%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20district%20judge%20in%20Colorado%20initially%20ruled%20that%20Trump%20did%20engage%20in%20insurrection%20but%20determined%20he%20should%20not%20be%20barred%20from%20the%20ballot.%20The%20Colorado%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20however%2C%20overturned%20that%20judge's%20ruling%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolorado-rules-trump-disqualified-from-2024-primary-ballot-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eproceeded%20to%20ban%20him%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BColorado%20has%20a%20real%20case.%20This%20is%20not%20a%20frivolous%20or%20completely%20off-the-wall%20argument%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Lemieux%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Washington%20and%20an%20expert%20in%20constitutional%20law%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20case%20stems%20from%20a%20small%20segment%20of%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20known%20as%20Section%203%2C%20which%20prohibits%20any%20%26quot%3Bofficer%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20from%20holding%20office%20if%20they%20%26quot%3Bengaged%20in%20insurrection%20or%20rebellion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20disqualification%20clause%20was%20originally%20meant%20to%20keep%20former%20Confederates%20from%20returning%20to%20the%20government%20after%20the%20Civil%20War.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20never%20directly%20ruled%20on%20the%20application%20of%20the%20clause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decision%20in%20the%20Trump%20case%20will%20likely%20come%20down%20to%20the%20court's%20definition%20of%20two%20terms%20included%20in%20the%20Amendment%3A%20%26quot%3Bofficer%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binsurrection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20legal%20perspective%2C%20this%20case%20presents%20a%20constitutional%20super-nova%3A%20A%20Constitutional%20provision%20with%20nearly%20no%20authoritative%20interpretation%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3B%20coupled%20with%20a%20former%20president%20who%20wants%20to%20occupy%20the%20position%20again%3B%20coupled%20with%20a%20state%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20holding%20to%20the%20contrary%2C%26quot%3B%20Doron%20Kalir%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Cleveland%20State%20University%20College%20of%20Law%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20many%20law%20professors%20could%20have%20concocted%20a%20more%20complex%20exam%20question%20in%20their%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65b0531d6c8f0a134f796e98%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%3Cp%3EScott%20Eisen%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOral%20arguments%20could%20foreshadow%20how%20the%20court%20is%20leaning%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECourt%20watchers%20may%20be%20able%20to%20infer%20how%20individual%20justices%20are%20thinking%20about%20the%20questions%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20case%20by%20tracking%20how%20they%20act%20during%20oral%20arguments%2C%20Lemieux%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20tell%20by%20the%20way%20their%20questions%20are%20framed%20or%20by%20how%20the%20justices%20try%20to%20pick%20apart%20arguments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20justices'%20attitudes%20could%20also%20offer%20early%20clues%20about%20whether%20the%20court%20is%20likely%20to%20vote%20along%20its%20ideological%20divide%20%E2%80%94%20a%20six-three%20conservative%20tilt.%20Three%20of%20the%20justices%20determining%20the%20case%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-lawyer-brett-kavanaugh-step-up-supreme-court-trump-colorado-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eappointed%20to%20the%20court%20by%20Trump.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20both%20Trump%20and%20the%20Colorado%20voters%20will%20have%20to%20address%20whether%20the%20disqualification%20provision%20applies%20to%20Trump%2C%20whether%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20was%20an%20insurrection%2C%20and%2C%20if%20so%2C%20whether%20Trump%20participated%20in%20the%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20defense%20is%20likely%20to%20focus%20on%20arguing%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-brief-remain-colorado-ballot-ahead-supreme-court-arguments-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eformer%20president%20was%20not%20an%20%26quot%3Bofficer%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20US%20when%20he%20was%20president%20and%20that%20he%20did%20not%20participate%20in%20insurrection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20for%20the%20former%20president%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bofficer%26quot%3B%20refers%20to%20executives%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%2C%20not%20the%20president%20himself%2C%20who%20is%20elected%20by%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeveral%20outcomes%20are%20possible%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20justices%20could%20rule%20against%20Trump%20and%20allow%20Colorado%20to%20proceed%20with%20its%20election%20without%20him%20on%20the%20ballot%2C%20though%20most%20election%20law%20experts%20have%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2024%2F02%2F07%2Fsupreme-court-trump-colorado-ballot-case%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ethis%20is%20an%20unlikely%20outcome.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlternatively%2C%20the%20top%20court%20could%20side%20with%20Trump%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%3A%20They%20could%20determine%20he%20did%20not%20engage%20in%20insurrection%20while%20president%3B%20he%20was%20not%20an%20%26quot%3Bofficer%20of%20the%20United%20States%26quot%3B%20while%20serving%20as%20president%3B%20or%20the%20court%20could%20dismiss%20the%20case%20on%20a%20technicality%2C%20determining%20only%20Congress%20has%20the%20power%20to%20enforce%20the%20clause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20could%20also%20determine%20a%20person%20needs%20to%20be%20charged%20and%20convicted%20of%20engaging%20in%20insurrection%20in%20order%20for%20the%20clause%20to%20apply%2C%20to%20uphold%20due%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20court%20may%20write%20the%20opinion%20as%20narrow%20and%20as%20wide%20as%20it%20would%20choose%2C%26quot%3B%20Kalir%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20those%20options%20give%20the%20court%20%26quot%3Boff-ramps%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20justices%20can%20avoid%20answering%20whether%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20was%20an%20insurrection%20and%20whether%20Trump%20engaged%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Supreme%20Court%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b18b1617692f0d03cdf08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Supreme%20Court%20building%3Cp%3ECelal%20Gunes%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarolyn%20Shapiro%2C%20founder%20of%20Chicago-Kent's%20Institute%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20said%20kicking%20the%20ultimate%20decision%20to%20Congress%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bthe%20worst%20thing%20they%20could%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20a%20clear%20answer%20to%20the%20question%20of%20Trump's%20eligibility%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20tol