y%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%20However%2C%20the%20404%20Media%20and%20CourtWatch%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereport%20notes%20that%20Roskin-Frazee%2C%20a%20security%20researcher%2C%20had%20reported%20issues%20to%20the%20tech%20giant%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20indictment%20filed%20in%20December%202023%2C%20the%20US%20Attorney%20in%20San%20Francisco%20charged%20Roskin-Frazee%20and%20a%20co-defendant%20with%20counts%20including%20fraud%20and%20intentionally%20damaging%20a%20protected%20computer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20allege%20in%20the%20indictment%20a%20complicated%20scheme%20that%20involved%20Roskin-Frazee%20and%20the%20co-defendant%20using%20a%20password%20reset%20function%20to%20break%20into%20the%20account%20of%20an%20employee%20who%20worked%20with%20Apple%20customers%20and%20then%20editing%20orders%20for%20things%20like%20gift%20cards%20and%20devices.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20edited%20the%20orders%20to%20come%20out%20to%20%240%2C%20or%20had%20gift%20cards%20sent%20to%20fake%20addresses%2C%20which%20they%20then%20resold%2C%20per%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20walked%20away%20with%20about%20%242.5%20million%20in%20products%2C%20services%2C%20and%20gift%20cards%2C%20according%20to%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Apple%20isn't%20named%20explicitly%20in%20the%20indictment%2C%20CourtWatch%20and%20404%20Media%20note%20that%20the%20indictment%20says%20the%20company%20is%20headquartered%20in%20Cupertino%2C%20California%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bdeveloped%2C%20manufactured%2C%20licensed%2C%20supported%20and%20sold%20computer%20software%2C%20consumer%20electronics%2C%20personal%20computers%2C%20and%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoskin-Frazee's%20attorneys%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F