ater%20harvesting%20technique%20known%20as%20Khambhati%20Kuva%20(Percolation%20well)%20was%20implemented.%20The%20well%2C%20with%20a%20diameter%20of%2010%20feet%20and%20a%20depth%20of%2030%20feet%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20collect%20rainwater%20and%20recharge%20the%20ground.%20This%20well%20can%20absorb%2045%2C000%20to%2060%2C000%20litres%20of%20water%20in%20just%20one%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUp%20and%20running%20since%202021%2C%20Anand%20says%20looking%20back%20at%20his%20work%2C%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20professional%2C%20I%20approach%20all%20projects%20with%20the%20same%20intensity.%20However%2C%20working%20on%20this%20project%20was%20unique.%20In%20our%20architectural%20education%2C%20we%20had%20never%20delved%20into%20questions%20about%20users%20to%20this%20extent.%20It%20opened%20my%20eyes%20to%20the%20realisation%20that%20in%20designing%20any%20building%2C%20be%20it%20public%20structures%20or%20entire%20cities%2C%20we%20must%20consider%20a%20diverse%20set%20of%20users%2C%20ensuring%20that%20none%20are%20excluded.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20lesson%20of%20inclusivity%20that%20I%20learned%20from%20this%20experience%20has%20profoundly%20influenced%20my%20approach%20to%20new%20projects%2C%20where%20I%20strive%20to%20incorporate%20the%20valuable%20insights%20gained%20from%20the%20school%20project.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(All%20image%20credit%3A%20SEAlabs)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706624472000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2Fschool-3-1706623026.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D340084%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Located%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20'School%20for%20The%20Blind%20and%20the%20Visually%20Impaired'%20is%20designed%20especially%20for%20children%20from%20remote%20villages%20of%20the%20state.%20The%20school's%20architecture%20incorporates%20the%20senses%20of%20smell%2C%20touch%2C%20hearing%2C%20and%20sight%20to%20help%20its%20pupils.%20Anand%20Sonecha%20of%20SEAlabs%2C%20the%20creative%20mind%20behind%20this%20distinctive%20design%2C%20elucidates%20the%20concept%20behind%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20This%20Inspiring%20%E2%80%9912th%20Fail%E2%80%99%20Has%20a%20Million%20Followers%20on%20Instagram%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20small%20village%20called%20Chitrakote%20in%20Nabarangpur%20district%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F326176%2Fodisha-triple-train-tragedy-women-cremate-unclaimed-bodies%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20Odisha%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20content%20creator%20has%20taken%20the%20internet%20by%20storm%20with%20just%20his%20smartphone%20by%20making%20reels%20about%20how%20to%20speak%20in%20English%20like%20an%20American.%C2%A0Despite%20a%20lack%20of%20formal%20education%20and%20failing%20his%20Class%2012%20examinations%2C%20Dhiraj%20Takri%E2%80%99s%20reels%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F327999%2Famerican-english-teacher-elizabeth-keyton-started-elikutty-to-learn-and-teach-malayalam-instagram%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20on%20Instagram%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehave%20made%20him%20a%20beloved%20teacher%20of%20conversational%20English%20online.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20unique%20approach%20involves%20incorporating%20snippets%20from%20web%20series%20and%20TV%20shows%20to%20make%20learning%20engaging%20and%20fun.%20Overcoming%20some%20initial%20trolling%2C%20Dhiraj%E2%80%99s%20follower%20count%20rose%20from%20160%20on%207%20December%202023%20to%201%20million%20on%2020%20January%202024%E2%80%94barely%2044%20days%E2%80%94on%20Instagram.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20over%201%20million%20followers%20today%2C%20Dhiraj%20has%20risen%20out%20of%20obscurity%20through%20his%20creativity%2C%20passion%20and%20desire%20to%20improve%20his%20communication%20skills%20by%20teaching%20others%20how%20to%20talk%20like%20a%20native%20English%20speaker%20despite%20lacking%20the%20resources%20that%20most%20content%20creators%20possess.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20Dhiraj%20to%20dig%20a%20little%20deeper%20into%20his%20magical%20journey%20on%20the%20internet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Dhiraj%20Takri%20(%40dhirajtakri)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELockdown%20opportunity%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20at%20a%20local%20village%20school%20till%20matriculation%20(Class%2010)%2C%20Dhiraj%20went%20to%20a%20nearby%20town%20to%20complete%20his%20intermediate%20(high%20school)%20but%20failed%20his%20Class%2012%20examinations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThings%20at%20home%20weren%E2%80%99t%20easy%20because%20our%20financial%20situation%20was%20unstable.%20My%20father%20used%20to%20repair%20bicycles%20while%20my%20mother%20travelled%20from%20one%20village%20to%20another%20selling%20bangles%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20jewellery.%20After%20taking%20my%20Class%2012%20exams%2C%20I%20went%20to%20Kerala%20for%20a%20year%20where%20I%20lived%20and%20studied%20at%20a%20Christian%20theological%20training%20institute%20in%20Thiruvalla%2C%20Kerala.%20The%20only%20requirement%20to%20study%20there%20was%20a%20matriculation%20certificate.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20his%20parents%20are%20unemployed%20but%20his%20elder%20brother%20runs%20a%20local%20Jan%20Seva%20Kendra%20(common%20services%20centre).%20These%20centres%20assist%20residents%20access%20essential%20services%20online%20such%20as%20Aadahaar%20and%20PAN%20card%20services%2C%20payment%20of%20household%20bills%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20a%20two-year%20course%2C%20he%20only%20studied%20there%20for%20a%20year%20because%20of%20the%20national%20lockdown%20imposed%20following%20COVID-19.%20It%20was%20at%20this%20institute%20where%20he%20started%20learning%20English.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20weren%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20regular%20access%20to%20our%20mobile%20phones.%20Every%20Saturday%2C%20they%20would%20allow%20us%20to%20use%20our%20phones%20for%20three%20hours.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20a%20smartphone.%20I%20had%20a%20Jio%20phone%20with%20basic%20features.%20During%20one%20such%20